Reasoning: The paper deals with image classification of ancient Roman Republican coins, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning methods and attention mechanisms suggests that it may also belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the challenges of uneven illumination and background clutter, which could indicate a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) or computer graphics (cs.CR) sub-categories.
